    Now, there's one interesting thing about being commanding a ship and how it compares to running an EQ guild. Analogy commences.<br>
    A <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> good</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ship captain acquires a swift understanding of his crew and each crewmember's abilities. He/she knows their strengths, their weaknesses, and how to fully utilize the former and minimize the latter. The crew learns to depend on each other to do their best in hard situations, because if they don't, all that's left is a big boat at the bottom of the ocean and a lot of dead people. If the captain spots negligence, or outright crime on his ship, he is quick to dispense justice, because such things can end up in the same situation mentioned in the previous sentence. (I REALLY hope I'm right Garthin...)<br>
